at.nineyards.anyline.modules.ocr

Interface AnylineOcrUiListener


  • public interface AnylineOcrUiListener

    A listener for UI relevant events that can be used with AnylineOcrHelper.

    If you are not sure that you need this, you may want to use AnylineOcrScanView instead, where this is already implemented.

    Note: This is interface is ALPHA and the API may change.

    Since:
    3.4.2

      • getTextHeightAdaptionFactor

        double getTextHeightAdaptionFactor()
        Should return a factor with which the min and max char height should be divided by to adapt set values to the really used resolution (e.g. if 1080p is configured but the phone supports 720p only this should be 1.5). Must be 1.0 if no scaling is required.
        Returns:
        scale factor for min and max char height
